![1652.jpg](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1613492320497-75M39O4C0TFREMDTVYM5/1652.jpg)

Hello Love Birds and Lonely Hearts! With the dust of Valentine's day 2021 finally settling, we decided to take a look a show that dissects love in all its various forms, from dealing with a bad breakup, to finding your soul mate. Harley Quinn, which debuted on the DCUniverse app in 2019 more heart than you expect, mixed with enough F-Bombs and gratuitous violence to appeal to the psycho in all of us. Join the Don and his guest of honor (his very own sister!) as the siblings tackle toxic relationships, stages of grief and whether couples clown make-up is the new wave in this review of Harley Quinn Seasons 1 & 2!

**Please** leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](../episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
